      • getCommandByType

        public static <A> ColorLocalCommand getCommandByType(java.lang.Class<?> a)
        This method is very useful. Create a command to create a given type of object, so the command is the name of the class, appropriately annotated with CommandClass, moreover, the configurable interface can also be implemented, which indicates when the configuration of a certain type of object is completed. The parameters of the command, will be the fields and methods of the class, obviously annotating everything with ParameterField and ParameterMethod. The symbol "£" acts as a space for the arguments (String) of a method, so to give as an argument for example "Hello World", we will do: -methodName hello £ world £ !! The final string will be: hello world !!
        Type Parameters:
        A - type
        Parameters:
        a - The class you want to convert into command
        Returns:
        the command
        See Also:
        Configurable, CommandClass, ParameterField, ParameterMethod
